8 months 🫶🏼 end of an era. We did it my sweet boy! 

Honestly, this isn’t my usual content so I’m sure it’ll raise some brows..but I’m truly SO proud of how far we made it with nursing. I’m proud of this photo too & will cherish it forever. BF was really tough for me in the beginning.. mentally & physically. I know it contributed to my PPD/PPA, but I told myself I’d give it a real solid chance & I’m so glad I did. I almost gave up a million times. It’s not for everyone, and I know not everyone has the option.. so I’m so grateful we did & never take it for granted 🥲🥺 A fed baby is a happy & healthy one! Asher is thriving on formula & I’m already noticing some extra squish hehe. 

K. Time for Botox HAHA jk jk.

Just a friendly reminder to myself 🖤🫶🏼 

as a new mama— I’ve had times where I’ve felt like I “lost a part of me” — maybe it’s my creative side or my successful side.. but that’s NOT true. They’re all lies. It may look & feel different, but this version of me is more fulfilled and living with more purpose. I’m overall a better version of ME and becoming a mama has been the greatest blessing. I love it so much & feel like I truly found myself. Even if my work shoots are interrupted by this tiny human and take 2x as long — I wouldn’t change it for the world 🌎🥹 ok end of rant. I was in my rollercoaster of feels earlier today & wanted to share just incase anyone else has felt this. #firsttimemom #motherhoodunplugged #vulnerability #contentcreator
